<item>
            <title>[CXF-5864] Anonymous users are denied to call unprotected methods since 2.6.3</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-5864</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Since &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-4495&quot; title=&quot;Extend SimpleAuthorizingInterceptor to check only configured roles&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CXF-4495&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CXF-4495&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (contained in CXF 2.6.3), anonymous users are denied to call unprotected methods.&lt;br/&gt;
The method &quot;handleMessage&quot; of the class &quot;AbstractAuthorizingInInterceptor&quot; now checks that the UserPrincipal is not null.&lt;br/&gt;
Any call results now into a AccessDeniedException.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;Caused by: org.apache.cxf.interceptor.security.AccessDeniedException: Unauthorized
	at org.apache.cxf.interceptor.security.AbstractAuthorizingInInterceptor.handleMessage(AbstractAuthorizingInInterceptor.java:57) ~[cxf-rt-core-2.6.3.jar:2.6.3]
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
